search:Java + Hibernate Envers:hibernate.content:
- **CLI Commands**: None required.
- **Latest Versions**:
  - Hibernate Envers: 6.2.3.Final
  - Spring Boot: 3.1.4
- **Key Config Options**:
  - `@EnableJpaAuditing` on main application class
  - Define entity classes with `@EntityListeners(AuditingEntityListener.class)`
  - Configure audit tables using `@AuditTable`
  - Customize revision entities with `@RevisionEntity`
  - Enable auditing in Spring Boot properties: `spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update`
- **Example Code Snippet**:
  ```java
  @Configuration
  @EnableJpaAuditing(auditorAwareRef = "auditorProvider")
  public class AuditConfig {
      @Bean
      public AuditorAware<String> auditorProvider() {
          return () -> Optional.of("system");
      }
  }

  @EntityListeners(AuditingEntityListener.class)
  @Entity
  public class MyEntity {
      @Id
      @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
      private Long id;

      // other fields

      @CreatedDate
      @Column(name = "created_date")
      private Date createdDate;

      @LastModifiedDate
      @Column(name = "last_modified_date")
      private Date lastModifiedDate;
  }
  ```
